p: Compound 4 was eluted out at 10.377 min and displayed the precursor ion at m/ z 255.06511 (C 15H 10O 4 [M+H] +) under positive ionization mode. An amount of secondary MS2 data, such as 119.04904 (C 8H 7O [M] +) and 121.02834 (C 7H 5O 2 [M] +), indicated that the compound 4 may be daidzein based on these results. Compound 4 was temporarily identified.
